Following February 26, the number of confirmed cases per day in South Korea fell below 300 for the first time, the South Korean government said the spread of new crown pneumonia in Taegu and North Gyeongsang Province has been effectively contained, judging that the epidemic has initially entered a stable stage. However, the government also stressed that there are still new cases of pneumonia in the country, should continue to focus on epidemic prevention efforts. South Korean Foreign Minister Kang Kyung Ho has pledged $3 million to the World Health Organization Organization as a global fund to fight the disease.

Xiao Bian today would like to focus on South Korea in the middle of the epidemic mortality problem. Let's start with two numbers: The infection density in South Korea is 738.20 cases per 10,000 square kilometers, and the infection rate is 1,429.51 cases per 10,000 people, much higher than in the provinces and cities other than Hubei. The case fatality rate in Korea is about 0.70% , which is lower than that in other provinces. The global case fatality rate is currently about 3.4% .

At the same time, there are three other reasons why South Korea can do this, besides the health system's success. First of all, the initial epidemic on the completion of the source of the "New World" Church and Daegu city delineation. Gyeonggi Province even "could not wait and did not fully believe" the list provided by the church and raided its headquarters. Second, on February 18, before the outbreak in Taegu, 8,923 people in South Korea were tested for nucleic acids, according to South Korea's Disease Management Ministry. About a week after the Daegu outbreak (as of 9:00 am on February 26) , nearly 10,000 more people have been tested for nucleic acids. Finally, NUCLEIC ACID testing in South Korea costs 100,000 won per person, or about 600 yuan. There is less economic pressure on the population and less resistance.
